Key Match Events: Marnus Labuschagne top-scored for Australia with 71 runs
Adam Zampa took 3 wickets for 21 runs and was player of the match
Chris Woakes took 4 wickets for 54 runs
Dawid Malan and Ben Stokes smashed half-centuries but England did not produce significant partnerships
Post-Match Reflections: England captain Jos Buttler said, 'To be stood in this position, having arrived in India with high hopes is incredibly tough and disappointing. It hurts a lot'
Australia captain Pat Cummins said, 'It’s been great. The boys have played brilliantly, every game we’ve found a way to win'
Miscellaneous Highlights: England were put in to bat
Australia managed 253 in reply to slump to their sixth defeat in seven matches and stay rooted to the bottom of the table
Others: The match was played at the Narendra Modi Stadium in Ahmedabad, India
The defending champions England were eliminated from the 50-over World Cup
